    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
        var arrReturnElements = new Array();
        strClassName = strClassName.replace(/\-/g, "\-");
        var oRegExp = new RegExp("(^|\s)" + strClassName + "(\s|$)");
        var oElement;
        for(var i=0; i<arrElements.length; i++){
            oElement = arrElements[i];
            if(oRegExp.test(oElement.className)){
                arrReturnElements.push(oElement);
            }
        }

    function hideAll(elems) {
      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';
      }
    }
    window.onload = function() {
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'table', 'vars'));

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);
      var s = link.getElementsByTagName('span')[0];
      var uarr = String.fromCharCode(0x25b6);
      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);
      s.innerHTML = s.innerHTML == uarr ? darr : uarr;
      return false;

    function switchPastebinFriendly(link) {
      s1 = "Switch to copy-and-paste view";
      s2 = "Switch back to interactive view";
      link.innerHTML = link.innerHTML == s1 ? s2 : s1;

<div id="summary">
  <h1>ValueError at /mirror/payment/</h1>
  <pre class="exception_value">Cannot assign &quot;2&quot;: &quot;Transaction.owner&quot; must be a &quot;User&quot; instance.</pre>
  <table class="meta">

    <tr>
      <th>Request Method:</th>
      <td>POST</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>Request URL:</th>
      <td>http://localhost:8002/mirror/payment/</td>

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
        var arrReturnElements = new Array();

      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';
      }

      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'table', 'vars'));

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);
      var s = link.getElementsByTagName('span')[0];
      var uarr = String.fromCharCode(0x25b6);
      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);
      s.innerHTML = s.innerHTML == uarr ? darr : uarr;
      return false;
    }

      link.innerHTML = link.innerHTML == s1 ? s2 : s1;
      toggle('browserTraceback', 'pastebinTraceback');
      return false;

              <ol start="57" class="context-line"><li onclick="toggle('pre2963026204', 'post2963026204')"><pre>        return view_func(*args, **kwargs)</pre> <span>...</span></li></ol>

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);
      var s = link.getElementsByTagName('span')[0];
      var uarr = String.fromCharCode(0x25b6);
      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);
      s.innerHTML = s.innerHTML == uarr ? darr : uarr;
      return false;

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
        var arrReturnElements = new Array();

            if(oRegExp.test(oElement.className)){

            }

      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';
      }
    }
    window.onload = function() {
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'table', 'vars'));

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);
      var s = link.getElementsByTagName('span')[0];
      var uarr = String.fromCharCode(0x25b6);
      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);
      s.innerHTML = s.innerHTML == uarr ? darr : uarr;
      return false;
    }

      s1 = "Switch to copy-and-paste view";
      s2 = "Switch back to interactive view";
      link.innerHTML = link.innerHTML == s1 ? s2 : s1;
      toggle('browserTraceback', 'pastebinTraceback');
      return false;
    }

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
        var arrReturnElements = new Array();

      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);

      var uarr = String.fromCharCode(0x25b6);
      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';

      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);

      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
        var arrReturnElements = new Array();
        strClassName = strClassName.replace(/\-/g, "\-");
        var oRegExp = new RegExp("(^|\s)" + strClassName + "(\s|$)");
        var oElement;
        for(var i=0; i<arrElements.length; i++){
            oElement = arrElements[i];
            if(oRegExp.test(oElement.className)){
                arrReturnElements.push(oElement);
            }
        }
        return (arrReturnElements)
    }
    function hideAll(elems) {
      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';
      }
    }
    window.onload = function() {
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'table', 'vars'));
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'ol', 'pre-context'));
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'ol', 'post-context'));
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'div', 'pastebin'));
    }
    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);
      var s = link.getElementsByTagName('span')[0];
      var uarr = String.fromCharCode(0x25b6);
      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);
      s.innerHTML = s.innerHTML == uarr ? darr : uarr;
      return false;
    }
    function switchPastebinFriendly(link) {
      s1 = "Switch to copy-and-paste view";
      s2 = "Switch back to interactive view";
      link.innerHTML = link.innerHTML == s1 ? s2 : s1;
      toggle('browserTraceback', 'pastebinTraceback');
      return false;
    }

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
        var arrReturnElements = new Array();
        strClassName = strClassName.replace(/\-/g, "\-");

        for(var i=0; i<arrElements.length; i++){

            }
        }

      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);

      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
        var arrReturnElements = new Array();
        strClassName = strClassName.replace(/\-/g, "\-");
        var oRegExp = new RegExp("(^|\s)" + strClassName + "(\s|$)");
        var oElement;
        for(var i=0; i<arrElements.length; i++){
            oElement = arrElements[i];
            if(oRegExp.test(oElement.className)){
                arrReturnElements.push(oElement);
            }
        }

    }

      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';
      }
    }
    window.onload = function() {
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'table', 'vars'));

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);
      var s = link.getElementsByTagName('span')[0];
      var uarr = String.fromCharCode(0x25b6);
      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);
      s.innerHTML = s.innerHTML == uarr ? darr : uarr;
      return false;

      s1 = "Switch to copy-and-paste view";

                <ol start='113' class="post-context" id="post2963687300"><li onclick="toggle('pre2963687300', 'post2963687300')"><pre>                except Exception as e:</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2963687300', 'post2963687300')"><pre>                    # If the view raised an exception, run it through exception</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2963687300', 'post2963687300')"><pre>                    # middleware, and if the exception middleware returns a</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2963687300', 'post2963687300')"><pre>                    # response, use that. Otherwise, reraise the exception.</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2963687300', 'post2963687300')"><pre>                    for middleware_method in self._exception_middleware:</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2963687300', 'post2963687300')"><pre>                        response = middleware_method(request, e)</pre></li></ol>
              
            </div>

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
        var arrReturnElements = new Array();
        strClassName = strClassName.replace(/\-/g, "\-");

        for(var i=0; i<arrElements.length; i++){

      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';
      }
    }
    window.onload = function() {
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'table', 'vars'));

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);
      var s = link.getElementsByTagName('span')[0];
      var uarr = String.fromCharCode(0x25b6);
      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);
      s.innerHTML = s.innerHTML == uarr ? darr : uarr;
      return false;
    }

      s1 = "Switch to copy-and-paste view";
      s2 = "Switch back to interactive view";
      link.innerHTML = link.innerHTML == s1 ? s2 : s1;
      toggle('browserTraceback', 'pastebinTraceback');
      return false;

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
        var arrReturnElements = new Array();
        strClassName = strClassName.replace(/\-/g, "\-");
        var oRegExp = new RegExp("(^|\s)" + strClassName + "(\s|$)");
        var oElement;
        for(var i=0; i<arrElements.length; i++){
            oElement = arrElements[i];
            if(oRegExp.test(oElement.className)){
                arrReturnElements.push(oElement);
            }
        }
        return (arrReturnElements)
    }
    function hideAll(elems) {
      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';
      }
    }
    window.onload = function() {
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'table', 'vars'));
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'ol', 'pre-context'));
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'ol', 'post-context'));
      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'div', 'pastebin'));
    }
    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);
      var s = link.getElementsByTagName('span')[0];
      var uarr = String.fromCharCode(0x25b6);
      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);
      s.innerHTML = s.innerHTML == uarr ? darr : uarr;
      return false;
    }
    function switchPastebinFriendly(link) {
      s1 = "Switch to copy-and-paste view";
      s2 = "Switch back to interactive view";
      link.innerHTML = link.innerHTML == s1 ? s2 : s1;
      toggle('browserTraceback', 'pastebinTraceback');
      return false;
    }

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);

      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';
      }
    }

      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'table', 'vars'));

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);
      var s = link.getElementsByTagName('span')[0];
      var uarr = String.fromCharCode(0x25b6);
      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);
      s.innerHTML = s.innerHTML == uarr ? darr : uarr;
      return false;

      link.innerHTML = link.innerHTML == s1 ? s2 : s1;

  <div id="explanation">
    <p>
      You're seeing this error because you have <code>DEBUG = True</code> in your
      Django settings file. Change that to <code>False</code>, and Django will
      display a standard 500 page.
    </p>

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
        var arrReturnElements = new Array();
        strClassName = strClassName.replace(/\-/g, "\-");
        var oRegExp = new RegExp("(^|\s)" + strClassName + "(\s|$)");
        var oElement;
        for(var i=0; i<arrElements.length; i++){
            oElement = arrElements[i];
            if(oRegExp.test(oElement.className)){
                arrReturnElements.push(oElement);
            }
        }
        return (arrReturnElements)
    }

      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';
      }
    }

      hideAll(getElementsByClassName(document, 'table', 'vars'));

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function varToggle(link, id) {
      toggle('v' + id);
      var s = link.getElementsByTagName('span')[0];
      var uarr = String.fromCharCode(0x25b6);
      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);
      s.innerHTML = s.innerHTML == uarr ? darr : uarr;
      return false;
    }
    function switchPastebinFriendly(link) {
      s1 = "Switch to copy-and-paste view";
      s2 = "Switch back to interactive view";
      link.innerHTML = link.innerHTML == s1 ? s2 : s1;
      toggle('browserTraceback', 'pastebinTraceback');
      return false;

          <code>/home/zdimon/hd/www/pressa_ve/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/django/views/decorators/csrf.py</code> in <code>wrapped_view</code>

          
            <div class="context" id="c2962735228">
              
                <ol start="50" class="pre-context" id="pre2962735228"><li onclick="toggle('pre2962735228', 'post2962735228')"><pre>    &quot;&quot;&quot;</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2962735228', 'post2962735228')"><pre>    Marks a view function as being exempt from the CSRF view protection.</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2962735228', 'post2962735228')"><pre>    &quot;&quot;&quot;</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2962735228', 'post2962735228')"><pre>    # We could just do view_func.csrf_exempt = True, but decorators</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2962735228', 'post2962735228')"><pre>    # are nicer if they don&#39;t have side-effects, so we return a new</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2962735228', 'post2962735228')"><pre>    # function.</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2962735228', 'post2962735228')"><pre>    def wrapped_view(*args, **kwargs):</pre></li></ol>
              
              <ol start="57" class="context-line"><li onclick="toggle('pre2962735228', 'post2962735228')"><pre>        return view_func(*args, **kwargs)</pre> <span>...</span></li></ol>
              
                <ol start='58' class="post-context" id="post2962735228"><li onclick="toggle('pre2962735228', 'post2962735228')"><pre>    wrapped_view.csrf_exempt = True</pre></li><li onclick="toggle('pre2962735228', 'post2962735228')"><pre>    return wraps(view_func, assigned=available_attrs(view_func))(wrapped_view)</pre></li></ol>

    function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName){
        // Written by Jonathan Snook, http://www.snook.ca/jon; Add-ons by Robert Nyman, http://www.robertnyman.com
        var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all)? document.all :
        oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
        var arrReturnElements = new Array();

      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';

      return false;

      var darr = String.fromCharCode(0x25bc);

  <div id="explanation">
    <p>
      You're seeing this error because you have <code>DEBUG = True</code> in your
      Django settings file. Change that to <code>False</code>, and Django will
      display a standard 500 page.
